                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d448">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">611.9331/71: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">MacMurray</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-07-27T10:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 27, 1928—10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received July 27—1:45 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>574. Your No. 240, July 26, 9 a.m. just received. Regret it is too late to change
                    arrangements made with Chinese who I understand have already left. The fact of
                    signature of treaty has also leaked out.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">MacMurray</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
